In this section, we will focus on estimating the average coefficient vector \(\E[\bbeta_i]\) in the heterogeneous coefficient model \(\eqref{linear:equation:lecture_model}\): \[\begin{equation}\label{linear:equation:averager_intro_model}
    y_{it} = \alpha_i + \bbeta_i'\bx_{it} + u_{it}, \quad i=1, \dots, N, \quad t=1, \dots, T.
\end{equation}\] We will explicitly separate the intercept term \(\alpha_i\) in order to have more transparent conditions on covariate matrices. In doing so, we assume that there is no constant term in \(\bx_{it}\).
